records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court ordered defendant to serve 135 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 15 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for work. Court stayed sentence to 10/16/15 at 5pm.

Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay all applicable court costs and fees by 4/14/16, or to be docketed as a civil judgment.

Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
